# Migration Walkthrough: Groq to Gemini 2.5 Flash

I have successfully updated the HawaSentinel application to use Google's Gemini 2.5 Flash model instead of Groq's Llama 3.

## Changes Made

### 🤖 Agent Update (`agent.py`)
- Updated the `HawaSentinelAgent` class to accept `gemini_api_key`.
- Changed the LLM endpoint to Gemini's OpenAI-compatible service: `https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai/chat/completions`.
- Set the model string to `gemini-2.5-flash`.
- Updated all internal logs and error messages to reflect Gemini usage.

### 🖥️ UI Update (`app.py`)
- Replaced the "Groq API Key" input with "Gemini API Key".
- Updated the environment variable source to `GEMINI_API_KEY`.
- Updated status labels to show "Live Mode (Gemini)".
- Ensured the agent is initialized with the new Gemini key.

### 🔧 Tools (`tools.py`)
- Verified that the tool schemas are compatible with Gemini's function calling expectations.

## Verification
- Checked all files for hardcoded "Groq" references and replaced them.
- Verified the API endpoint URL for Gemini's OpenAI-compatible interface.
